lerics Please Read</span><hr size=1> Just wanted to toss out something that we need to consider as we grow up. With the size of our guild and the number of high level people that currently are active and raiding with the guild we have to look at changing some of our tactics. <br>
So I ask... <br>
Do you think that with a raiding party of 6-7 groups that we should keep using the MA on one and mezz everything else tactic will continue to be efficient?<br>
<br>
Could we coordinate multiple groups for faster movement through a zone?<br>
<br>
Can we coordinate better class attack methods or strategies to defeat mobs faster? <br>
<br>
How about setting up casters to use mana more efficiently instead of a all out blitz when full trying to get the experience?<br>
<br>
Can we improve the way we handle buffing? ie.. one cleric who is not a main healer does the buffs, identify what buffs will be used during the raid. ie.. Symbol, Heroic Bond, Focus plus haste and C2 and do not worry about anything else.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts?<br>
